{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"550ae881-1475-4cf5-8f98-f95c33dff8b3","content":"\n\nHere's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package (version matching your xunit version, e.g. 2.9.3):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (in a `<PropertyGroup>`):\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n4. **Optionally** enable the new output (recommended):\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformShowTestsFailure>true</TestingPlatformShowTestsFailure>\n   ```\n\n5. Run your tests with `dotnet test` as usual.\n\n> **Note:** `xunit.runner.mtp` replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio` — they shouldn't coexist. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e7439fb1-0a6a-47bf-8821-6a70217d9243","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":350},"id":"1bdd5296-b123-47ed-800f-92ba82e0d4f8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:41:13.479Z","parentId":"b0fe6b59-2fa8-49bd-9565-cc6b33c18991"}
